==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunbird
<hw>Sun"bird`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any one of numerous species of small brilliantly
colored birds of the family <fam>Nectariniidae</fam>, native of Africa,
Southern Asia, the East Indies, and Australia. In external appearance
and habits they somewhat resemble humming birds, but they are true
singing birds (Oscines).</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The sun
bittern.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunblink</ent>⟦br⟧
